Alter Race Issues

Problem

alter race was not asked in a variety of situations

We HAVE alter race for all active partnerships. For MALE EGOS, we HAVE race for all previous cohabs and marriages. We also have a few one-time partner races for MALES if the one-time partner was their most recent partner.

We DO NOT HAVE alter race for any inactive partnerships or one-time partnerships for females. We DO NOT HAVE alter race for inactive “others” for males. We DO NOT HAVE alter race for male one-time partners that were not their most recent partner.

Imputation

proposal: impute partner race for missngs

Males:
- impute missing “other” inactivces based on reported active “other” - impute missing one-times based on most recent one-times

Females:
- impute all inactives based on active distribution (cohab/marriages 1 dist, others another dist) - impute missings one-times based on transposed male one-time responses

current questions - are female reports of mixing different by cohab/marriage versus other? are male reports of active cohab/marriage different than inactive marriage/cohab?
